<p>At the moment I'm using this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="SidebarRow"&gt;         &lt;asp:TextBox ID="TextBox1" runat="server"&gt;     &lt;/asp:TextBox&gt;&lt;asp:ImageButton ID="ImageButton1" ImageUrl="~/calendar.png" runat="server" Height="25" Width="25" /&gt;        &lt;ajaxToolkit:CalendarExtender ID="CalendarExtender" TargetControlID="TextBox1" runat="server" PopupButtonID="ImageButton1" /&gt;        &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p><code>TargetControlID</code> is  appending the date to <code>TextBox1</code> but I would like to use three textboxes each for day month and year. I was thinking of hiding the <code>TextBox1</code> and splitting the date.</p>  <p>Solution: I added before <code>&lt;/body&gt;</code></p>  <pre><code>&lt;script&gt;     $('[id$=TextBox1]').change(function () {         if ($(this).val().length &gt; 2) {             date = $(this).val();             $(this).val(date.substring(0, 2));             $('[id$=TextBox2]').val(date.substring(5, 3));             $('[id$=TextBox3]').val(date.substring(6));         }     }); &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The initial date is 19/09/15 and now is separated as it should. </p>